1 3. Robbery with a dangerous weapon;
2 4. Rape in any degree;
3 5. Arson in the first degree;
4 6. Shooting with intent to kill;
5 7. Manslaughter in the first degree;
6 8. Forcible sodomy;
7 9. Any felony conviction for which the evidence shows that the
8 defendant used or was in possession of a firearm or other dangerous
9 or deadly weapon during the commission of the offense;
10 10. Trafficking in illegal drugs;
11 11. Manufacturing a controlled dangerous substance;
12 12. Abuse against an intimate partner as defined by Section
13 60.1 of this title;
14 13. Abuse of a child;
15 14. Sexual abuse of a child; or
16 13. 15. Any other felony after former conviction of a felony.
17 The granting or refusal of bail after judgment of conviction in
18 all other felony cases shall rest in the discretion of the court;
19 provided, however, if bail is allowed, the trial court shall state
20 the reason therefor for granting bail.
21 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
